{"source_key":"sha256-852da461b9759bc2736926d9891eb9a3","record_index":9245,"record_hash":"sha256:f4979b69c424c34c06670e99069c9dc26fd44eb99fe1ae9af2b5e12d453b013d","timestamp":"2026-05-20T18:00:25.208Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"user","text":"<subagent_notification>\n{\"agent_path\":\"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\"status\":{\"completed\":\"**Findings**\\n\\n- [cli.rs:453](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/cli.rs:453) `associated_sessions_outputs_verified_sessions` is too weak for the new CLI contract. It only checks first session key and `turn_keys.len() == 1`; it does not assert `target_kind`, normalized `target_key`, exact `sessions.len()`, or the actual `turn_key`. Smaller stronger version: make `write_turn_with_targets()` return the turn key, then assert the exact serialized shape for one branch query.\\n\\n- [cli.rs:475](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/cli.rs:475) `associated_session_target_key_normalizes_common_inputs` covers only unprefixed inputs. The risky regressions are double-prefixing already-normalized values: `ref:refs/heads/main`, `refs/heads/main`, `gitbutler-review:x`, `gitbutler-change:x`. I’d make this a compact table test and include those cases; that’s the whole value of this helper.\\n\\n- [gitmeta/tests.rs:468](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta/tests.rs:468) `find_related_sessions_returns_verified_turn_keys` only proves one session can be returned. The user-facing question is “what sessions are associated with target?”, plural. Stronger missing test: two sessions, same branch, each with one related turn, assert both `RelatedSession`s and exact per-session turn keys. That would protect the primitive better than adding more CLI assertions.\\n\\n- [cli.rs:453](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/cli.rs:453) CLI and GitMeta tests overlap a bit. Keep GitMeta responsible for “verified hits / stale hits / ordering”; keep CLI responsible for “arg parsing, normalization, output shape.” Don’t add another deep CLI fixture test for review/change, since `find_related_sessions` already owns target semantics.\\n\\n- [gitmeta/tests.rs:727](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta/tests.rs:727) Minor cleanup: this combines “unrelated target” and “wrong session” in one test. Not worth changing alone, but if touching the file, split it or pick the more important one. Right now a failure would be slightly noisier than needed.\"}}\n</subagent_notification>","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T18:00:25.208Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"user"}}}